text: Les Hauts de Forterre is a commune. It is in Bourgogne-Franche-Comté in the Yonne department in central France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2017 and consists of the former communes of Taingy (the seat), Fontenailles and Molesmes.Arrêté préfectoral 16 August 2016 == References == * INSEE Category:2017 establishments in France Category:Communes in Yonne
title: Les Hauts de Forterre
